<h2 id="what-is-kilo">📋 What Is Kilo?</h2>

Kilo is a gym-specific CRM and marketing automation platform designed to capture, nurture, and convert fitness leads into paying members. Founded in 2018 and headquartered in San Francisco, the platform has evolved from a simple lead tracking tool into a comprehensive marketing suite that handles everything from initial ad integration to long-term member retention campaigns.

The platform integrates directly with Facebook and Google ad accounts, pulling lead data in real-time and triggering automated follow-up sequences. Unlike generic CRMs that require extensive customization for fitness businesses, Kilo comes pre-built with gym-specific workflows, lead scoring models, and communication templates.

Core capabilities include multi-channel lead nurturing (SMS, email, voicemail drops), appointment scheduling, pipeline management, and detailed attribution reporting. The 2026 version introduced AI-powered lead scoring and predictive analytics that estimate lifetime member value at the lead stage.

Kilo competes directly with platforms like <a href="/reviews/gymleads-review-2026">GymLeads</a> and general-purpose tools like HubSpot, but positions itself as the middle ground between enterprise complexity and basic spreadsheet tracking.

<h2 id="our-experience">🏋️ Our Experience Managing Gyms With Kilo</h2>

Our team has deployed Kilo across CrossFit affiliates, boutique fitness studios, and large-format gyms over the past four years. Collectively, we've managed implementations at over 40 locations using this platform, giving us direct visibility into what works and what breaks at scale.

The initial setup experience improved dramatically in 2025. Earlier versions required significant hand-holding from Kilo's support team to configure lead sources properly. The current onboarding wizard handles most integrations automatically, and we've seen operators go from signup to live campaigns within 48 hours.

Where Kilo truly shines is lead response time automation. In our experience, the gyms using Kilo's instant-response features see 3x higher contact rates compared to locations relying on manual follow-up. When a lead submits a form at 11 PM, they receive a personalized text within 90 seconds. That immediate engagement window drives conversions.

We've also stress-tested Kilo during high-volume periods. During January campaigns across multiple locations, one operator pushed 2,400 leads through the system in a single week. The platform handled the volume without degradation, though we noticed SMS delivery delays of 2-3 minutes during peak hours.

The reporting dashboard has become essential for our multi-location operators. Being able to compare lead source performance, staff follow-up rates, and conversion metrics across all locations from a single view eliminates hours of manual data compilation.

