<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features Breakdown</h2>

<h3>Lead Capture & Integration</h3>

Kilo connects natively with Facebook Lead Ads, Google Ads, Instagram, TikTok Ads, and most landing page builders. The webhook system handles custom integrations for operators using less common lead sources. Lead data syncs in under 30 seconds in our testing, which matters when speed-to-contact determines conversion rates.

The platform includes built-in landing page templates optimized for gym offers. While not as flexible as dedicated builders like <a href="/reviews/leadpages-vs-clickfunnels-gyms">Leadpages or ClickFunnels</a>, they're sufficient for standard free trial and intro offer campaigns.

<h3>Automated Nurture Sequences</h3>

The sequence builder uses a visual workflow editor that non-technical staff can manage. Pre-built templates cover common gym scenarios: intro offer follow-up, no-show recovery, trial-to-member conversion, and win-back campaigns for churned leads.

Multi-channel sequencing works well. You can trigger an immediate SMS, follow with an email two hours later, drop a ringless voicemail the next morning, and assign a manual call task if no response occurs. The conditional logic handles responses intelligently—when a lead replies to a text, the system pauses automation and alerts staff.

<h3>Appointment Scheduling</h3>

The built-in scheduler eliminates the need for separate tools like Calendly or Acuity for intro appointments. Leads book directly from SMS links or email buttons, and the system handles confirmation reminders automatically.

Calendar sync with Google and Outlook works reliably. The 2026 update added buffer time settings between appointments and location-specific availability, both features our team requested after managing high-volume booking scenarios.

<h3>AI Lead Scoring (2026 Feature)</h3>

The new predictive scoring system analyzes lead behavior patterns, demographic data, and historical conversion data from your gym to assign quality scores. After 90 days of data collection, the model becomes reasonably accurate at predicting which leads warrant immediate personal attention versus automated nurture.

We tested this across three locations over six months. The AI correctly identified high-value leads (those who converted to 12+ month memberships) with 72% accuracy. Not perfect, but useful for prioritizing staff time.

<h3>Attribution & Reporting</h3>

The reporting suite tracks leads from first touch through membership signup and beyond. Multi-touch attribution shows which combination of channels and touchpoints influenced conversions, not just last-click data.

Custom report builders allow operators to create location-specific dashboards. Our team particularly values the staff performance reports that show individual follow-up rates, response times, and conversion percentages—essential for coaching sales teams.

